critical_positive: I think we were able to find things in common and continue the conversation or relate that way. We were both interested in what the other said and able to ask follow-up questions to keep it going. We covered several topics and didn't really have to work too hard to find something to talk about.
critical_negative: When we ran out of content for a particular topic of conversation it was a bit awkward to make a transition or ask another question about something else since we didn't know each other. At the beginning it was a little awkward to get started, and then at the end it was awkward because we were more concerned about meeting the time limit.

begin_memory_text: I'm definitely not remembering most of the conversation, but we talked about work and what we both do/did.
middle_memory_text: We talked about where we live and where we grew up.
end_memory_text: We talked about traveling. I honestly can't remember much aside from that. I know I mentioned converting a school bus into a tiny home and she spoke briefly about her friend who did similar with a van.
rest_of_day_open: I'm going to Nebraska tonight with my husband to get our school bus! We'll be there until tomorrow afternoon and I'm hoping we'll be able to see at least one local attraction, because I haven't been to this part of Nebraska before. critical_positive: We both were really polite to each other and wanted to keep the conversation going. We tried to find common ground to elaborate on, like hobbies, jobs, pets (cats in particular), etc. It seems that we are both around the same level of "conversationally friendly", which helps in having simple discussions like this.
critical_negative: I had to fill in a lot of gaps where it was obvious that neither one of us knew how to proceed in the conversation. Honestly, I hate having to do that, because it causes a lot of stress for me to try to rapidly come up with new topics that seem to fit the other person's interests. I'm still trying to learn how to deal with scenarios like this, even at my age.
